org.qbroker.monitor

Class Monitor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.qbroker.monitor.Monitor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MonitorAction, MonitorReport
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AgeMonitor, ChannelMonitor, DBQuery, DBRecord, ExpectedLog, FileComparator, FileMonitor, IncrementalMonitor, JMSHealthChecker, JMSLogMonitor, JMSMonitor, JMXQMonitor, JVMMonitor, LatestRecord, MultiFileMonitor, NumberMonitor, ProcessMonitor, PropertyMonitor, QMFQMonitor, QueueMonitor, RMQMonitor, ScriptLauncher, ServiceMonitor, SonicMQMonitor, SyntheticMonitor, UnixlogMonitor, URLMonitor, WebOperator, WinlogMonitor

    public abstract class Monitor
extends java.lang.Object
implements MonitorReport, MonitorAction
    Monitor is an abstract class with partial implementation of both MonitorReport and MonitorAction. It has two abstract methods, generateReport() and performAction(). Other methods can be overridden if it is necessary.
    Author:
    yannanlu@yahoo.com

                                                                         throws java.lang.Exception
        Description copied from interface: MonitorReport
        generates a report on a monitored entity and returns it as a Map. The report Map will be passed to the associated MonitorAction as an opaque object. The action object is supposed to know how to retrieve the information from the report Map.
